</title>
<subSubSection id="BEC300BBE46C3819A64D37204AF2E8F0" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph id="4A4BCF3DF59EE2D50EF806BD83EAED7F" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="9116808504D4B86EF9E82873D0ED9766" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Anthericum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="liliago">
<emphasis id="A6F6F209F1E1B87FDAB4826799D3E51F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">A. Liliago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="74D7760EBB22DD60134F3483EF1775F0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<normalizedToken id="0AD159576CA5EF22E6A0B8F4D14420F9" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
verzweigt, auch 
<normalizedToken id="4E652B2A39F5781B7D402AEC8337C263" originalValue="seitenständige" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">seitenstaendige</normalizedToken>
Trauben vorhanden; 
<normalizedToken id="C2AC450F31491C27AAAB652B479420F6" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
0,8-1,3 cm lang, die innern deutlich breiter als die 
<normalizedToken id="735299EB5411C819E06C9805DB1606B1" originalValue="äuβern" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">aeuβern</normalizedToken>
; Frucht kugelig
</emphasis>
, Durchmesser 5-7 mm; 
<emphasis id="7E856658A616AB0D24166CF5D686A732" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Griffel</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="5552F660F1AAAF8FEC07CBF2E4723704" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">+/-</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="8D0B56F194AA36BC7E49DD14600E271D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
gerade, 
<normalizedToken id="07A073C2A73A2BE8CC16EF4383C4D024" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die 
<normalizedToken id="4C23D46E3286235ECBCF82F9C7607957" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
. -
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="23D1E602FAF61B430267D64B6EE18F14" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3548053969EA1BF4492F5CE94598D5E" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="D32320B725CF97EBB744840C28679AFE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="1D2F261A0911852ABE411F917E3611F3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">30:</emphasis>
Material aus Scania, 
<normalizedToken id="013D34735D0972E3D6D48DCFF9053A63" originalValue="Südschweden" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Suedschweden</normalizedToken>
(Strandhede 1963). 
<emphasis id="B4A6C819D9E394D453EE97615AA94D4B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="FD5CEB7FF16A96689038D06003926C86" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">32:</emphasis>
Material aus botanischen 
<normalizedToken id="2B5DF44FABD741C371E65DE82E369E00" originalValue="Gärten" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Gaerten</normalizedToken>
; Meiose und Embryosackentwicklung untersucht (Stenar 1928, Elvers 1932), aus Ungarn (
<normalizedToken id="0F0426F7D0F9597E0B5427E9D0FA0023" originalValue="Pólya" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Polya</normalizedToken>
1950, Baksay 1956), aus 
<normalizedToken id="1DE622116057EA3ABAB1CCED5AED5DCB" originalValue="Dänemark" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Daenemark</normalizedToken>
(Holmen in 
<normalizedToken id="C313FD49384F0D826A4E1B75F0FE0067" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="CAFB199B117113AF7A4ECB062A731EFA" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1961), aus dem 
<normalizedToken id="F653BB1BA0824EBA6BC8AD188CCC912F" originalValue="Elsaß" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Elsass</normalizedToken>
(vgl. Gagnieu et al. aus 
<normalizedToken id="02A6A68EC6EE443A9CA5947230637DB3" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="E2812797369FE0EE42C2BFB608659384" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1961).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725D1642D37064965C23AA1441FFFDF1" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B2BDAD1469BA2104793AC3740FD9AB64" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin und montan, selten subalpin. Trockene, kalkhaltige 
<normalizedToken id="7315430D06B2D3981D96B7910037AF51" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in warmen Lagen. 
<emphasis id="647D472A5C94549EF27B99C7AD5C7FC9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicName id="BE462D6121D494352E34819931068F99" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bromus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Bromus</taxonomicName>
erectus-
</emphasis>
Wiesen, lichte 
<emphasis id="F9E6572447CF60C16223E22D45254DF3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicName id="AEE463D73AB93F0758DC2D4A651BE505" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pinus</taxonomicName>
silvestris-
</emphasis>
und 
<emphasis id="42A4BFDD19BCB078CCD82086942B28FD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicName id="F34FBB16FB85A052878371C1A6E5095E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
sessiliflora-
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="C02EE9F8E0BD5484E7B76E110EB37EAE" originalValue="Wälder" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Waelder</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D53116A3EB1F2B99E5E284C42FE15ECD" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="6A839188CD33A5086B74A60F3BACBA93" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="7C5743992BD3ADAA3A49D39B61496777" originalValue="Europäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Europaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="5A5A7E0ED80CEE3EB02D3F09E9E6205E" originalValue="Nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
vereinzelt bis Belgien, Norddeutschland, 
<normalizedToken id="D17426385D02E63569B3D9097D1338DB" originalValue="Südschweden" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Suedschweden</normalizedToken>
; Mittelund 
<normalizedToken id="9DC285E75ADBF13026F541BA5C1D3680" originalValue="Südrußland" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Suedrussland</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="E5E7BB668CE8F1E75C04A160DC43C3F6" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis ins Donaugebiet und in den Kaukasus; 
<normalizedToken id="BC3D7E142689416F860D0E9EC8D35A14" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis 
<normalizedToken id="0565AF0C6779AE04B583CDCC9F92AB25" originalValue="Pyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Pyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
(?), Abruzzen, Mazedonien, 
<normalizedToken id="AF4AF773E598C8D9BCD6E321CB025505" originalValue="europäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">europaeische</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="D6A2885A0F497E8E1A8027AF17689ED8" originalValue="Schwarzmeerküste" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Schwarzmeerkueste</normalizedToken>
. Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - Im Gebiet ziemlich verbreitet, nicht 
<normalizedToken id="5465EA4CD6FCFA5704754F7AA0A00F7B" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
